Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Agathokles. Same die used for an example from Paphos, Nikolaou 125, no. 296. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0762)
